Ingestion Layer README

Unified Device → Metric Normalization System

“One Contract. Any Device. Infinite Intelligence.”



🔥 Overview

The ingestion layer is the front door of the Athlete Performance Intelligence System.  
Its job is simple:

> Take any device’s raw data → convert it into one universal Metric[] format → feed BiomechFlow + dashboards + NIL engines.

Apple Watch, WHOOP, Catapult, GPS trackers — everything collapses into the same internal shape.

This guarantees:

- Consistent analytics  
- Predictable BiomechFlow node behavior  
- Plug‑and‑play device support  
- Zero downstream rewrites  



🧠 Core Concepts

1. Metric Contract (The Universal Shape)
All devices normalize into the same structure:

- source → where the data came from  
- type → what the metric represents  
- value → numeric reading  
- unit → normalized unit  
- timestamp → ISO  
- meta → raw vendor details  

This is the only shape the intelligence engine consumes.


2. Device Adapters (The Plug‑In System)
Each device vendor implements the same interface:

- canHandle(input) → routing  
- toMetrics(input) → normalization  

Adapters live in:

`
/src/ingestion/adapters
`

Add a new device?  
Just drop in a new adapter file — no other code changes required.


3. Ingestion Router (The Dispatcher)
The ingestion router selects the correct adapter and returns Metric[].

`
normalizeDevicePayload(input) → Metric[]
`

This is the single entry point for all device data.


4. Device Profile (Auto‑Configuration Layer)
Once metrics are ingested, the system builds a DeviceProfile:

- Detects which devices are active  
- Configures UI tiles  
- Adjusts BiomechFlow weighting  
- Enables/Disables readiness modules  



